   "shields": "1D",
   "of_note": "Skill: Archaic starship piloting. Backup hyperdrive: x15. The Lore Seeker reflects her current captain well — the aging ship combines modern practicality with the romance and grace of a bygone era. When the Lore Seeker arrives in port, old trader captains sigh wistfully remembering their youth and even busy port authorities take a moment to admire the sleek ship nestled among the squat blocky freighters. Originally a Hyrotil Engineering in-system pleasure yacht with maneuverable solar sails (sensitive radiation collectors let captains pilot in all but the outermost reaches of a system, and particularly adept pilots could thread their way through multi-star systems by trimming sails to maximize thrust from one star while minimizing another — Hyrotil even produced a sails-only variant for the Old Republic sailship race circuit, though the sport has largely died out). Tionne's modifications: small hyperdrive engine added, sublight engine upgraded (both at the expense of cargo area and crew/passenger quarters), single laser cannon in the nose for defense against pirates and asteroids, sensors modernized but not upgraded. The shield generator will not work while the sails are extended — they break up shield integrity. Retracting the sails takes about one minute; extending them takes about half that. Tionne took pains to preserve the ship's original appearance — aside from the laser cannon (a 'regrettable necessity') the modifications have not appreciably altered its original lines. Collectors have offered Tionne a handsome sum for the ship but she views it as her home and cannot bear to part with it. It has survived the Exis Station firestorm incident and delivered Tionne and Luke Skywalker safely back to Yavin 4 along with a priceless cache of Jedi data plaques including Nomi Sunrider's Convocation speech.",
