   "shields": "4D (normally 8D)",
   "of_note": "Heavily damaged during the Battle of Tantive V. Running on skeleton crew. Hyperdrive inoperative. Backup hyperdrive inoperative (normally x10). All weapons fire control reduced to 0D. Weapons and tractor beams at reduced numbers. Crew skill: capital ship piloting 6D+2, starship shields 5D+2, starship sensors 5D, astrogation 4D, capital ship gunnery 6D. | THE SOULLEX YEARS / TWO FOR ONE INCIDENT (AJ#15): The Guardian spent over a decade in limping orbit around the obscure Outer Rim world of Soullex (which hosted three prefab Imperial garrisons of about 10,000 troops total), with Admiral Drommel slowly sending Lambda-class shuttles into Imperial-controlled systems requesting hyperdrive repair parts. New Republic probe droids eventually noticed the pattern, and General Airen Cracken dispatched the brand-new two-being Special Acquisitions Unit (Cryle Caw and Sienn Sconn) to capture the ship intact. The SAU operatives intercepted the shuttle parts delivery at Sensyno Station on the Vohai Unirail, infiltrated the Guardian disguised as stormtroopers with the help of a snarky CT-EX protocol droid called 'Teex,' sabotaged the hyperdrive (which still had ~36 hours to repair completion under Drommel's new accelerated timeline), were captured during the sabotage, escaped, freed New Republic Intelligence operative Shandria L'hnnar from Detention Block 220, and rigged the Guardian's first test hyperjump to drop into a New Republic ambush of one Star Cruiser, two Corvettes, and an Escort Frigate under Captain Volahn of the Equity. After his hyperjump test landed in the trap, Drommel ordered his crew to execute everyone — but his second-in-command Colonel Niovi shot him dead on the command walkway and immediately surrendered the Guardian and its entire crew to the New Republic. Crew at the time of capture: ~250,000, of whom about 40,000 were trained combatants. The Guardian is now a New Republic asset.",
