   "of_note": "Standard Plexus droid courier vessels — small unmanned 9-meter hyperspace runners — quietly delivered to the Imperial military shipyards at Jaemus and undergoing extensive secret modification by a Renikco cover company under Santhe Security guard. The interior is gutted and refitted with miniaturized navigational and maneuver controls, an astrogation nav computer, an acceleration control couch, and a small life-support enclosure just large enough to house a single human-sized passenger — specifically a Death-Hunter cyborg. The exterior receives a starfighter-sized laser cannon and an elaborate hollowed half-moon heat shield up front, of the type normally seen on probe droid drop pods, hinting at planetary insertion roles. The combination is the delivery system for Moff Jesco Comark's Death-Hunter project: programmed cyborgs are loaded into the vessels and dispersed across hundreds of systems simultaneously to hunt down Rebel spies and Alliance leadership without the chain-of-command headaches the Imperial Navy associates with bounty hunters. The Renikco modification dock at Jaemus uses Moff Comark's personal authorization for visitor screening and is one of the highest-security private docks in the shipyards.",
