   "of_note": "Captain Heedon's avian-lined SoroSuub Luxury Cruiser 200, painted in pleasant unmilitary shades of blue with the name Starcrossed scrolled across her side in elegant slanting letters. Built as a getaway ship for the galaxy's affluent — not as transport, but as a destination in herself: spacious suites, in-cabin meals, gourmet kitchens, an entire-deck holotheater in the round, a casino/gambling deck, and an elegant ballroom for dancing. Decks include a dining room, casino, holo-theater, kitchens, holo control booth, engineering access, staff quarters, guest cabins, crew quarters, cargo bays, escape pods, and a boarding deck with hatch. Once a thriving luxury cruise business catering to wealthy aristocrats, the operation collapsed under Palpatine as the aristocracy was gutted; Heedon now places himself and his ship at the disposal of the Rebellion in hopes of restoring the Republic — and, more importantly to him, his clientele. The ship is too large to fit a Victory-class Star Destroyer's docking bay, a quirk Sayer Mon Neela exploited during the capture of the Imperial Hazard above Horob, forcing the Imperials to grapple Starcrossed with a docking claw and umbilical corridor.",
