   "shields": "",
   "of_note": "Captain Sergus Lanox's Victory-class Star Destroyer, sent to Horob to extinguish a Rebel research base hidden inside a planetside medical clinic. Above Horob the Hazard fell for Sayer Mon Neela's bluff that the SoroSuub luxury yacht Starcrossed was rigged to detonate, accepting a docking-claw conference via umbilical corridor (the yacht was too long to fit a Victory-class docking bay). During the conference Neela's bodyguard Stasheff was wired with an experimental Horob sensor chip that recorded the Hazard's detention codes and all 10 of its tractor beam projector codes; once Stasheff returned to the Starcrossed, Heedon dumped the chip into the comm board and the data flooded back into the Hazard's systems hundreds of times per second, sending the ship's computers into a full power loop, dropping its altitude toward the planet, and trapping the Hazard in a self-inflicted brace of overloads. The umbilical corridor partially decompressed and ruptured during a series of explosions; Captain Lanox survived by crawling the length of the failing corridor back to his ship just as Starcrossed broke for hyperspace. The Hazard ultimately stabilized in orbit, listed helplessly, and was widely reported destroyed — but Imperial state media spun the loss as Lanox's heroism in the face of 'the latest and most heinous example of Rebel terrorism since the destruction of Alderaan,' for which Grand Admiral Takel personally awarded him the Distinguished Medal of Imperial Honor.",
