   "of_note": "[2 ABY] Admiral Thrawn's exile command — the Imperial-class Star Destroyer assigned to him after his fall from Imperial Court favor. Carries Thrawn's hand-picked complement of officers and personnel, including Captain Dagon Niriz (commanding officer), Commander Voss Parck (first officer / Thrawn's adjutant), General Larr Haverel (ground forces commander), and at least one squadron of new hyperdrive-equipped TIE scouts. Outfitted with a full TIE fighter wing, three sensor-stealthed assault shuttles (the Specter group), and at least one Zeta-class long-range shuttle (specifically requested by Thrawn for his Unknown Regions sojourn — likely intended for use should the alien admiral ever be summoned back to Coruscant on short notice). Officially tasked with mapping and surveying the Unknown Regions; in practice the mission appears to be exile imposed on Thrawn and anyone vaguely associated with him after the Imperial Advisors and their factions briefly united against the alien admiral. Yet Thrawn acts as if he is still diligently serving the Emperor, treating every obstacle as an intriguing challenge — and seems to know exactly where they are going in their survey, as if searching for something specific. The Admonitor's first major intelligence victory came at her fifteenth surveyed system, where she 'colony-shipped' her way into a contact with the Ebruchi pirate captain Creysis, baited him with a transponder-rigged sculpture and a 'captured' TIE/Zeta delegation, then jumped to lightspeed and routed an entire Ebruchi clan fleet at their headquarters.",
