   "of_note": "Zeta-class shuttles are long-range personnel transports built more for speed and distance than for combat maneuvers. Originally included in the starship complement of Victory-class Star Destroyers, they have since been widely replaced throughout the Imperial Fleet by the newer, more versatile Lambda-class shuttles. The Zeta is a blocky transport with large port and starboard fuel 'tanks' — external storage containers holding additional fuel cells and life-support components for particularly long journeys. The tanks are modular and can quickly be removed and replaced with fresh ones during stopovers on urgent flights. Admiral Thrawn specifically requested at least one Zeta-class shuttle for the Star Destroyer Admonitor during his sojourn into the Unknown Regions; some of his support staff assumed it was intended for use if Thrawn were ever summoned back to Coruscant on short notice — if the alien were ever recalled from exile and forgiven. During the Ebruchi pirate confrontation at the Admonitor's fifteenth surveyed system, a Zeta shuttle carried Commander Voss Parck and six unarmed troopers as bait into Creysis's command ship, where boarders later breached the starboard fuel tank with explosives during the rescue. Crew skill: astrogation 3D+2, space transports 4D+2.",
