   "of_note": "Captain Amarith's personal ship — a SoroSuub Luxury 2800 yacht (the precursor to the Luxury 3000), 37 meters long, covered with opaque transparisteel windows and a polished glistening hull. The ship's previous owner was a Ho'Din crime lord whom Captain Amarith ran out of business during a clash between his organization and the Alliance; she took a liking to the vessel and claimed it for the Alliance. Used as a mobile base by the crime lord, the Gambit appears to be a typical pleasure vessel — but improved shield generators, concealed weapons (a double laser cannon hidden in the nose and a retractable blaster cannon in a turret), a re-vamped sensor array, and carefully reinforced hull plating make it the perfect vessel for covert insertion missions while still passing customs as a tourist yacht. The interior remains posh and comfortable enough to deceive even an astute customs inspector. A concealed compartment in the aft storeroom (Very Difficult search to find) holds a covert-ops kit for deep-cover Rebel operatives: blaster pistols, detonite blocks, remote fuses and timer detonators, blaster power packs, fragmentation grenades, comlinks, a PS-9 burst tracker, datapads, a pocket computer, medpacs, fast-flesh medpacs, and macrobinoculars. Forged travel passpads and an entire wardrobe of expensive tourist clothes are stored openly. Standard mission load includes eight breath masks. Captain Amarith loaned the Gambit out for the Ando Project insertion mission against the Empire's secret aquaculture facility on Uridia.",
