   "of_note": "If the bulk freighter and the container ship are the work-banthas of the SoroSuub Transport and Supply Division, the Nyubba-class cargo barge driver is the work-nerf. Smaller ships like the Nyubba freighters still account for nearly 20% of all SoroSuub's cargo transfers — slow and lightly armed, they manage to get the job done but make excellent targets for pirates if they stray from designated shipping lanes. They are almost fully automatic, requiring a crew of only two to monitor ship systems and handle landing/take-off. Additional cargo barges (Hull 5D, 400 metric tons each) can be attached fore and aft of the barge driver since the freighter's main engines are offset on a lateral strut. The average configuration is the main engine with three barges fore and three aft, though more are not uncommon. Add +1 to the difficulty of any space transports roll for each of the first eight barges, then +1D for each barge past eight. There is a long-standing rivalry among Nyubba-class pilots over who can haul the most barges over a prescribed distance — Bungo Bung's Chubby Gundark holds the standing record: 13 barges hauled over three parsecs (with an uncontrolled landing).",
